Everton will face Dynamo Kiev in the last 16 of the Europa League after the draw was made in Nyon, Switzerland on Friday.

The Toffees beat Swiss side Young Boys 3-1 at Goodison Park on Thursday night, completing a 7-2 aggregate win after an impressive 4-1 victory in Bern last week.

Roberto Martinez's side now face a two-legged tie against the Ukrainian outfit in March, with a trip to Kiev on 19.

