There was an all-Spanish flavour to the draw as well after Villarreal and Sevilla were picked to face-off, while Rafael Benitez's Napoli will be pleased they play Dinamo Moscow. 

Zenit St Petersburg, managed by former Tottenham and Chelsea boss Andre Villas-Boas, are to play Torini.

Besiktas - who beat Liverpool on penalties in the last 32 - will travel to Club Brugge for their first leg.

